review.review: The out of the box experience isn't great - ear pads are uncomfortable out of the gate and take a couple of weeks to really break in. Mic monitoring is horrid at default settings, and while it can be corrected you have to connect to a computer and run updates - not what you're looking for in a piece of console hardware.Once the ear cups are broken in and you've done the updates, these will be acceptable for a while, with only a few annoyances like random de-syncing... and then the headband will just randomly break one day while you're wearing the headset. review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 22, 2021
review.title: Nice 4 Price - I’m A Poet
review.review: It’s never been easier to scream at 12 year olds from across the globe! People complain that I sound like a robot sometimes but I think that might just be a personal issue or the fact that Xbox controllers are designed to fail especially when accessories are used with them or just my potato-powered router. Either way, this headset makes me happy for the most part. Second time purchasing in a few years. My cat destroyed the pop filter on my last one and tore up the wire coating and it still worked for a while after that. If you want something that is super high quality then pls stop complaining about this headset because it’s legitimately the best one you can buy at this price and you can save your lunch money for another month to get a sicker one with all the bells and whistles. But if you’re feeling uptight about this headset then please take your snootiness somewhere else, because as long as the complete strangers that absolutely wreck me in my mediocre pub CoD lobbies can disrespect my entire family in 2 sentences or less and I can hear it, and they can hear me audibly crying because I forgot to turn my mic off with the very easy to understand mute switch on these bad boys, I’m extremely fine with this product. 5 stars because you’re either first or your last and since I bought this product twice, I’m either dumb or it’s just that good. Prove me wrong, Dennis!

review.title: Wow... what a piece of trash
review.review: And now is a time for a tale of woe... I ordered this hard drive system at the same time I ordered one for my TV based pc game system. As soon as I got it I saw that there was a problem it requires a side panel that somehow had fallen off my Xbox to be used to a fix the hard drive box too, so I ordered a replacement OEM side panel had to wait several weeks to get it and by that point I was into a game on my PC system so I attached it the hard drive for the Xbox and booty it up enough to see that the hard drive was being recognized. Unfortunately what I didn't know was there was a bad connection in the add-on box and the hard drive was visible but not usable also that the USB ports did not carry any power. When I finally got around to using my Xbox I thought that my Xbox was having problems it went black screen of death and after a couple of days of trying to get that fixed I finally found the problem which was the add-on box was causing problems with the Xbox and that the add-on box was underpowered and couldn't access the hard drive properly and none of the USB outlets could carry power even though they are color marked as USB 3 powered... Overall I'd call this device a piece of trash

review.title: Best Budget option for next gen gaming
review.review: Very affordable next gen system came with everything you need for budget high powered gaming system. Comes with the console much smaller than the x box one much easier to store and fits very easily on a shelf or desk, a free HDMI chord, a power chord and a controller which feels much durable than previous x box box controllers. The console does have a cooling fan on top which makes for longer gameplay without overheating and the only downside to the console which isn’t really a downside if you hate going in public is the system doesn’t have a insert slot to put physical copies of your gaming disk. Overall a great gaming system with great performance at a lower cost. You may need to buy more storage for this system if you’re a true gamer like me for hours and hours of gaming fun :)

review.title: Useful Tool
review.review: I bought this thinking I needed to transfer files from old Xbox One to new Xbox One X but found out all files are uploaded to cloud. I later use this to store games that I normally install/uninstall so I placed a few favorite games I'll replay w/o the hassle of either choice. I was able to store games like Dead or Alive 5 Last Round w/ 507 characters + costumes which on internal hard drive will cause a slow lag so it was store on this external hard drive instead and Dead or Alive 6 w/ 217 characters + costumes. I read reviews on external hard drive with pros and cons so it's no big deal if it messes up later or last a lifetime.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2021
review.title: Fast But Weird Setup
review.review: I was really wanting this from the time I bought my Xbox Series X and finally got it. 1 terabyte is just not enough storage, and frankly, this additional terabyte hardly slakes my thirst for more storage. Games are getting so big, now, I may still have to add USB storage.This device is fast. Load times are noticeably faster. But the set up is weird. The instructions come in the way of a simple graphical sheet that seems to indicate you just plug it in, so I did what most people would do and powered down my unit and plugged this in. After powering up, I transferred some of my games and apps from the internal drive to this without problem.However, when I went to play a game or start an app that I had transferred to the Seagate, I got an error that it would not run. After some sleuthing online, I found someone in a forum relating that he was told to leave the power on while plugging in the device. So I powered down the Xbox, took the Seagate out, powered up the Xbox, and while powered up, crossed my fingers and plugged in the Seagate.All was right in the world and it's been working fine ever since.
product.title: Seagate (STEA4000402) Game Drive for Xbox 4TB External Hard Drive Portable HDD – Designed for Xbox One ,Green

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2021
review.title: It works
review.review: This gets 5 stars because it functions as it should… but there are some things to note for the cheap people like me.1. It comes with a couple Duracell batteries which is nice but the device itself does not have an inner battery than can be charged via usb-c.2. When plugged in (to my pc running windows 10) it works perfectly fine but there is always a Microsoft Visual C++ Runtime Error that pops up and I haven’t troubleshooted it yet because it doesn’t seem to affect the functionality of the controller.3. It does not work with my cheap wireless dongle that plugs into the pc. Given that the cheap dongle I have was an absolute nightmare to get working with 360 controllers in the first place, this didn’t surprise me but is worth noting if you don’t have Bluetooth and want to be wireless.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 14, 2021
review.title: Fun challenging game
review.review: Cool realistic game with tons to do. Awesome vehicle upgrades and tasks giving you hours of play time. I'm 33 and with truck driving experience it's a riot to play. Haul big loads and small loads to complete jobs. Explore rugged terrain and near impossible swamps. Realistic damage, gearing, diff locks, motor upgrades, suspension and tire upgrades. Slowly teaching my 7 and 8 year old boys how to traverse the game. It has a glitch every now and then causing it to freeze up but no progress gets lost with the save points. Updating my ps4 seems to have resolved the freezing issue.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on September 7, 2021
review.title: An amazing and enthralling game
review.review: I keep seeing people who didn't read the description writing bad reviews on this... Read the reviews. It's not a fake, fly through the mud in some super powered vehicle Sim game. This game is the "Dark Souls" of simulators. Snowrunner seems slightly easier to me than the previous title (maybe just because I'm used to the game play now?), but they have a Hard Mode that changes the game play and makes it quite enjoyable for people who want to drag it out and keep more difficulty. :) Highly recommend and if you like it get the season 1 DLC at least. For 25 bucks (current going price of the DLC m) you get a LOT more maps content than even came with the original game. Season two isn't fully out yet, but I assume it will be the same level of content. We'll worth it for the entertainment value if you like this one. 😁
product.title: Snowrunner (Xb1) - Xbox One

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on July 11, 2021
review.title: Good idea, poor execution.
review.review: I wanted to drive one of their trucks in the winter snow, just like the truck shown on the package. I started in a small truck in Black River Michigan mud, and never got out of Black River Michigan mud. Documentation in the game is totally lacking in explanation, direction, and is not helpful.Apparently the game expects you to carry out tasks in a certain order. On the fifth time through I knew the tasks but not the order. So I could not do the tasks in any order. e.g. I arrive at a destination (bridge) with a loaded truck, but there is no way to unload it and check off the task. I briefly tried a snow setting, and I could not get more than 100 ft. game distance. (You figure the kilometers).
